8. Local vs Shared Reality Protocol

Principle:
Local reality can be chosen more than shared reality.
Shared reality requires checks.

def reality_check(belief):
    local_power = belief.effect_on_behavior()
    shared_validity = test_against([
        "evidence",
        "other observers",
        "repeatability",
        "consequences",
        "falsifiability"
    ])
    if local_power > 0 and shared_validity < threshold:
        return "use_as_myth_not_map"
    return "usable_model"

Output:
Confidence can manifest behavior.
Evidence determines whether the world joins you.

